		cmDynamicParameterRecord OBJECT-TYPE
			SYNTAX OCTET STRING
			ACCESS read-write
			STATUS mandatory
			DESCRIPTION
				"Record containing dynamic cable modem data:
				(format uint32 / network byte order unless otherwise noted)
				docsIfDownChannelFrequency (Rx center frequency in Hz, as in 1.3.6.1.2.1.10.127.1.1.1.1.2)
				docsIfDownChannelQamMode  (Rx modulation type, as in 1.3.6.1.2.1.10.127.1.1.1.1.4)
				docsIfDownChannelPower (Rx power in 0.1 dBmV, as in 1.3.6.1.2.1.10.127.1.1.1.1.6): CM reports to this docsIfDownChannelPower but amplifier adds offset to this.
				docsIfSigQSignalNoise (Rx S/N ratio in 0.1 dB, as in 1.3.6.1.2.1.10.127.1.1.4.1.5)
				docsIfUpChannelId (Tx CMTS identification, as in 1.3.6.1.2.1.10.127.1.1.2.1.1)
				docsIfUpChannelFrequency (Tx center frequency in Hz, as in 1.3.6.1.2.1.10.127.1.1.2.1.2)
				docsIfUpChannelBandwidth (Tx bandwidth in Hz, as in 1.3.6.1.2.1.10.127.1.1.2.1.3)
				docsIfCmStatusTxPower (Tx power in 0.1 dBmV, as in 1.3.6.1.2.1.10.127.1.1.1.1.6)
				docsIfCmStatusValue (CM communication status, as in 1.3.6.1.2.1.10.127.1.2.2.1.1)
				cmSystemTime (System POSIX time, MSB first)
				cmIfAddress (format: IpAddress)
				docsIfDownChannelPower (original value received from CM; only new amplifier softwares supports this field)"
			::= { cmConfig 2 }

		
		-- 1.3.6.1.4.1.3715.100.999.3
		cmStaticParameterRecord OBJECT-TYPE
			SYNTAX OCTET STRING
